    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and<strong> sliced shallot </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy veg stock</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek and shallot have softened, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>flour </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>creamy veg stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce to heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Tear your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until crisp and golden \u2013 these are your<strong> croutons</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash, then add your <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, add your <strong>salmon flakes</strong>, <strong>capers</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped dill </strong>(save some for garnish!) and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>spinach </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soured cream </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Scandi-style salmon & dill chowder</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scandi-style-salmon-and-dill-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Scandi-style salmon & dill chowder</strong> and top with the <strong>croutons</strong></p><p>Dollop over the <strong>remaining soured cream </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped dill</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
